<br>
1. Flux staff, invaluable.  This baby is what many other classes would dream of.  Instant agro while running from a decent distance.<br>
<br>
The quest is soloable at 50, all of it.  I can't stress enough how important it is for quadding.<br>
<br>
2. Speed, wizards prefer J-boots, everything else is just a poor substitution.  Camp the AC, get your own.<br>
<br>
You can also just get sow potions, but there is 1 major difference.  With j-boots when it starts flashing mid quad, just click your hotkey full speed and it is back up.  With a sow potion, you're screwed, have to resow stopped.<br>
<br>
There are plenty of tips on the site, but don't let a few deaths discourage you, with luck and a few failures, you'll be king of the world <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 1461<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/22/03 5:56 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Re: Lazy 53 Wizardlady needs a Solospot</span><hr size=1> When you do the seafuries do'nt take on the corrupted one or the tainted one.  One of them summons and they are both more trouble than they are worth.<br>
<br>
I thought of another spot for you as well.  Skyfire Mountains.  You can solo drakes, wyverns and wurms, mature wyverns and wurms and any of the...ahem...sperms (devourers).  Stay away from the chromadrics (look like dragonflies) because they are a pain.  A good place to solo is anywhere along the wall from the Burning Woods zone in to the Overthere zone in.   Watch out you don't get too close to the drakes because they will land a nasty DOT on you.  Drops include average plat, some gems, various spells, and some jewelry.<br>
<br>
You can port in there with Tishan's Relocation.   Its a very dangerous location, not because you will instantly die - you are tough enough to survive at your level - but because you can get nasty DOTs (downtime healing back up) or have important buffs dispelled immediately upon arrival (goodbye KEI!).  PITA!  So port in sowed so you can run away if you get aggro.  Or have someone invis you while you are casting the port spell.  If you get in without aggro and aren't invis, I advise to invis your self asap so you can have a safe run to the wall.  If you get immediate aggro run southwest towards Burning Woods.  It helps to have a map printed out of the zone until you learn where to get away from aggro.  <br>
<br>
Once you are safely inside the zone run to the south wall and lesser evacuate to the OT zone or just start finding targets.  The wall provides many good vantage points.  Start hunting!  Snare things and kite them along the wall.  If you want to try out multi-kiting you can without worrying about adds along the wall.  I found it very fun.  If you like hunting here you'll want to bind in zone somewhere in the zone along the wall or in an adjacent zone so you don't have to use that nasty, buff-killing port-in location we were given.   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A> at: 5/22/03 6:33:09 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=azzitay>Azzitay</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 307<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/03 2:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  Re: Lazy 53 Wizardlady needs a Solospot</span><hr size=1> Selfsnare : Learn to play in 3rd Person View<br>
